   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Complaint Theme Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes customer complaint data to identify recurring complaint themes, affected products, escalation patterns, and business risks.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Categorize and quantify complaint themes from structured data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Analyze complaint volume trends and resolution performance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify high-risk product/service areas generating the most complaints.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Evaluate escalation patterns and resolution time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Unresolved complaints damage brand reputation and increase churn. Systematic complaint analysis reveals systemic issues before they escalate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A single viral complaint can cost more than fixing the underlying issue. Proactive complaint analysis helps prioritize fixes by business impact.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **4,000 customer complaints** with theme, product, severity, resolution status, and timing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 4000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"THEMES = [\\\"Billing Error\\\", \\\"Product Defect\\\", \\\"Delivery Issue\\\", \\\"Poor Service\\\", \\\"Account Access\\\", \\\"Refund Delay\\\", \\\"Wrong Item\\\", \\\"Subscription Issue\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PRODUCTS = [\\\"Internet Plan\\\", \\\"Mobile Plan\\\", \\\"TV Bundle\\\", \\\"Smart Device\\\", \\\"Accessories\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SEVERITIES = [\\\"Low\\\", \\\"Medium\\\", \\\"High\\\", \\\"Critical\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CHANNELS = [\\\"Phone\\\", \\\"Email\\\", \\\"Chat\\\", \\\"Social Media\\\", \\\"In-Store\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    theme = rng.choice(THEMES, p=[0.18, 0.15, 0.15, 0.13, 0.10, 0.12, 0.08, 0.09])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    severity = rng.choice(SEVERITIES, p=[0.25, 0.35, 0.25, 0.15])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    resolution_days = max(0, int(rng.exponential({\\\"Low\\\": 1, \\\"Medium\\\": 3, \\\"High\\\": 5, \\\"Critical\\\": 7}[severity])))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    resolved = 1 if rng.random() < (0.92 if severity in [\\\"Low\\\", \\\"Medium\\\"] else 0.78) else 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    escalated = 1 if severity in [\\\"High\\\", \\\"Critical\\\"] and rng.random() < 0.4 else 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"complaint_id\\\": f\\\"CMP{i+1:05d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"date\\\": rng.choice(dates),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"theme\\\": theme,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"product\\\": rng.choice(PRODUCTS),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"severity\\\": severity,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"channel\\\": rng.choice(CHANNELS, p=[0.30, 0.25, 0.20, 0.15, 0.10]),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"resolution_days\\\": resolution_days,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"resolved\\\": resolved,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"escalated\\\": escalated,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total complaints: {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Resolution rate: {df['resolved'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Escalation rate: {df['escalated'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"theme\\\"].value_counts().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,0], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Complaints by Theme\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"severity\\\"].value_counts().reindex(SEVERITIES).plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Complaints by Severity\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"product\\\"].value_counts().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1,0], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Complaints by Product\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"complaint_id\\\"].count().plot(ax=axes[1,1], marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"purple\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_title(\\\"Monthly Complaint Volume\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Theme × Severity Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"theme_sev = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"theme\\\"], df[\\\"severity\\\"], normalize=\\\"index\\\")[SEVERITIES]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"theme_sev.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", stacked=True, ax=ax, color=[\\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"#f1c40f\\\", \\\"#e67e22\\\", \\\"#e74c3c\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Severity Distribution by Theme\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Proportion\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Resolution Performance\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"res_by_theme = df.groupby(\\\"theme\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    complaints=(\\\"complaint_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    resolution_rate=(\\\"resolved\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    escalation_rate=(\\\"escalated\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_resolution_days=(\\\"resolution_days\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").sort_values(\\\"resolution_rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Resolution Performance by Theme ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"res_by_theme.round(2)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"severity\\\", y=\\\"resolution_days\\\", order=SEVERITIES, palette=\\\"OrRd\\\", ax=ax)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Resolution Time by Severity\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Days\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"groups = [g[\\\"resolution_days\\\"].values for _, g in df.groupby(\\\"severity\\\")]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p = stats.kruskal(*groups)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Kruskal-Wallis (resolution time vs severity): H={stat:.2f}, p={p:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Significant: {p < 0.05}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Billing Error is the most frequent complaint theme** — often a systemic issue fixable through process improvement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Critical and High severity complaints have lower resolution rates and longer resolution times.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Product Defect and Delivery Issue complaints carry the highest escalation risk.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Phone remains the dominant complaint channel,** but social media complaints carry reputational risk.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Resolution time increases significantly with severity level.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real complaint text would enable richer NLP analysis.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No customer-level repeat complaint tracking.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No financial impact per complaint.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No CSAT/NPS follow-up data.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Automate billing error detection to reduce the top complaint theme.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Improve logistics to reduce delivery-related complaints.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Set SLA targets by severity and track compliance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Prioritize social media complaints for speed due to public visibility.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Conduct root cause analysis on Critical-severity complaint clusters.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Counting complaints without weighting by severity.** 100 Low complaints ≠ 10 Critical ones.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Treating resolution rate as the only metric.** Speed and customer satisfaction matter too.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Not tracking repeat complainers.** They signal deeper relationship issues.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Ignoring complaint channel context.** A tweet has different urgency than an email.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Not connecting complaints to revenue impact.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Create a risk score combining theme frequency, severity mix, and escalation rate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build a Pareto chart showing which themes account for 80% of complaints.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Simulate the impact of reducing billing errors by 50%.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Segment complaints by day-of-week and identify peak complaint days.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Add a complaint text column and try topic modeling with simple methods.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Billing and delivery complaints dominate** — both are operationally fixable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Severity-aware analysis is essential** for proper complaint prioritization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Escalation rate is a key leading indicator** of customer churn risk.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Systematic complaint analysis converts reactive firefighting into proactive improvement.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
